    <text><body>
            <div type="writingSession">
                <pb n="1r"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline><placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0005589 https://www.geonames.org/2650225">Edinburgh</placeName> August
                        29/51.</dateline>
                    <salute>My dear &amp; venerable friend</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Again I have to thank <lb/>you for a very long<supplied cert="high">,</supplied>
                    kind &amp; <lb/>instructive letter, full of
                    <lb/>valuable counsel, &amp; which I <lb/>shall treasure no less for its
                    <lb/>own sake, than for the <lb/>purpose of following the advice <lb/>you honor
                    me by giving.</p>
                <p>The Receipt from M. <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003264 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118509470">Profr. <lb/>Berghaus</persName> is
                    most acceptable – <lb/>I am quite sure that those <lb/>formerly sent must be
                    safe <lb/>somewhere, perhaps in the <lb/>hands of my <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011993 http://d-nb.info/gnd/11698094X">Father</persName>’s Bankers<pb n="1v"/>or elsewhere – any how, he has
                    <lb/>never received them &amp; regrets <lb/>equally with myself the trouble
                    <lb/>you &amp; <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003264 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118509470">Profr. Berghaus</persName> have
                    <lb/>been put to.<space dim="horizontal"/> I write to <lb/>that gentleman by
                    this opportunity, <lb/>&amp; take the liberty of enclosing <lb/>the letter to
                    you: – it authorizes <lb/>him to proceed with the work <lb/>so admirably begun,
                    &amp; to forward <lb/>the remainder to <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011993 http://d-nb.info/gnd/11698094X">Sir <choice>
                            <abbr>W.</abbr>
                            <expan>William</expan>
                        </choice> Hooker</persName>, <lb/>who will pay over the <measure quantity="75" unit="pfund_sterling">£ 75</measure>
                    <lb/>on their receipt, to any houses <lb/>M. <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003264 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118509470">Berghaus</persName> may direct.</p>
                <p>M. <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011923 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118863703">Hodgson</persName> writes frequently, <lb/>he is
                    still in very bad health<supplied cert="high">,</supplied>
                    <lb/>the Liver seriously affected &amp;<pb n="4r"/>possibly the smaller
                    intestines <lb/>also – he remains at <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0017337 https://www.geonames.org/1273467">Dorjiling</placeName>.</p>
                <p>The Presidents of the <orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000583 http://d-nb.info/gnd/39272-8">Royal</orgName>, <lb/><orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H5235692 https://d-nb.info/gnd/6632-1">Geo<subst>
                            <del rendition="#ow">g</del>
                            <add place="across">l</add>
                        </subst>ogical</orgName> &amp; <orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H6654236 https://d-nb.info/gnd/38819-1">Linnaean
                        Societies</orgName>
                    <lb/>waited upon <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H5870163 https://d-nb.info/gnd/1070103497">Lord Seymour</persName>, with <lb/>a
                    Memorial in my favor, <lb/>signed by upwards of 100 Men <lb/>of Science –
                    requesting that I <lb/>might be placed in a position <lb/>that would enable me
                    to <lb/>publish the results of my <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0006686 https://www.geonames.org/1269750">India</placeName>n <lb/>voyage<choice>
                        <orig>.</orig>
                        <reg>,</reg>
                    </choice> i.e. to give me a small <lb/>Salary for 3 years (say <measure quantity="300" unit="pfund_sterling">£ 300</measure>) to <lb/>enable me to
                    devote my time <lb/>to the subject, &amp; incur the necessary <lb/>expenses of
                    an author – but <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H5870163 https://d-nb.info/gnd/1070103497">Lord <lb/>Seymour</persName> (who is
                    First <orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0020402 http://d-nb.info/gnd/817272-9">Commissioner <lb/>of the Woods &amp;
                        Forests</orgName>, under whom <lb/>I travelled for <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000407 https://www.geonames.org/2645740">Kew</placeName>) has not<pb n="4v"/>vouchsafed any answer at all <lb/>to th<subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">e</del>
                        <add place="across">o</add>
                    </subst>se eminent men<choice>
                        <orig>,</orig>
                        <reg/>
                    </choice>
                    <del rendition="#s">though</del>
                    <lb/>(<persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0001066 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117595888">Lord Rosse</persName>, Mr <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003693 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118674455">Brown</persName> &amp; Mr <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011996 http://d-nb.info/gnd/116981806">Hopkins</persName>)<choice>
                        <orig/>
                        <reg>,</reg>
                    </choice>
                    <lb/>who waited on him 2½ months <lb/>ago.<space dim="horizontal"/> The <orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000533 http://d-nb.info/gnd/5300-4">British Association</orgName>
                    <lb/>have now taken it up, &amp; Mr <lb/><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0012547 http://d-nb.info/gnd/116274646">Airy</persName>, the President, heads a <lb/>deputation on the subject to
                    <lb/>the <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0001149 http://d-nb.info/gnd/116711086">Prime Minister</persName>, when he
                    <lb/>applies for various money grants <lb/>recommended by the <orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000533 http://d-nb.info/gnd/5300-4">Association</orgName>.</p>
                <p>Meanwhile the <orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0020395 http://d-nb.info/gnd/125636-1">Admiralty</orgName>
                    <lb/>empl<subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow"><gap reason="covered" unit="chars" quantity="1"/></del>
                        <add place="across">o</add>
                    </subst>y me for 3 years in <lb/>publishing <ref xml:id="f9f40897-3f89-4dc4-b408-973f895dc4ff" corresp="#d1f688ce-ed32-4da7-b688-ceed324da7c5" type="editorialNote">Floras of <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0001615 https://www.geonames.org/2186224">New Zealand</placeName>
                            <lb/>&amp; <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0009100 https://www.geonames.org/2147292">Van Diemen’s
                            Land</placeName></ref><note xml:id="d1f688ce-ed32-4da7-b688-ceed324da7c5" corresp="#f9f40897-3f89-4dc4-b408-973f895dc4ff" type="editorial"><bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/T5SDE24E">Hooker, J.
                                D. 1844–1860</bibl>, II und III.</note>, similar <lb/>to the <ref xml:id="db0a0857-db4d-4947-8a08-57db4d79476d" corresp="#f353c010-1aef-4cdd-93c0-101aef3cddd2" type="editorialNote">Antarctic Flora</ref><note xml:id="f353c010-1aef-4cdd-93c0-101aef3cddd2" corresp="#db0a0857-db4d-4947-8a08-57db4d79476d" type="editorial"><bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/T5SDE24E">Hooker, J.
                                D. 1844–1860</bibl>, I.</note>, &amp; I shall <lb/>have about <measure quantity="150" unit="pfund_sterling">£ 150</measure> a year from <lb/>that source<choice>
                        <orig>.</orig>
                        <reg>,</reg>
                    </choice> which is all my <lb/>present income. My abundant <lb/>leisure I shall
                    employ as you<pb n="2r"/>advise, in preparing my travels <lb/>for speedy
                    publication, this will <lb/>cost <hi rendition="#u">me</hi> nothing, or very
                    little, <lb/><subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">though</del>
                        <add place="superlinear">but</add>
                    </subst> as I want the <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0014458 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117624047">Publisher</persName>
                    <lb/>to <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">pr</del>
                        <add place="intralinear">bring</add>
                    </subst> out a very cheap <lb/>book, &amp; <subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow"><gap reason="covered" unit="chars" quantity="1"/></del>
                        <add place="across">y</add>
                    </subst>et copiously illustrated <lb/>with wood-cuts, I shall not <lb/>expect
                    any-thing, for the first <lb/>edition at any rate. A small <lb/>form (8<choice>
                        <orig> </orig>
                        <reg/>
                    </choice><hi rendition="#sup">vo</hi> or impe<supplied cert="high">r</supplied>ial 12<choice>
                        <orig> </orig>
                        <reg/>
                    </choice><hi rendition="#sup">mo</hi>)<add place="intralinear">,</add> with
                    <lb/>an abundance of wood engravings <lb/>of remarkable natural objects<choice>
                        <orig>,</orig>
                        <reg/>
                    </choice>
                    <lb/>(on which I have employed my <lb/>pencil<choice>
                        <orig>,)</orig>
                        <reg>),</reg>
                    </choice> Diagrams, Sections &amp;c, <lb/>appears to me the best form <lb/>of
                    combining instructiveness <lb/>with cheapness – &amp; I have three <lb/>sep<choice>
                        <orig>e</orig>
                        <reg>a</reg>
                    </choice>rate divisions to treat of <lb/><note place="mTop" hand="https://edition-humboldt.de/#addressee"><foreign xml:lang="fra"><ref xml:id="f726e635-bd5c-4d23-a6e6-35bd5c4d239a" corresp="#fc79d1a9-36a5-4295-b9d1-a936a5129513" type="editorialNote">Plaines du <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0009370 https://www.geonames.org/1279685">Thibet</placeName></ref><note xml:id="fc79d1a9-36a5-4295-b9d1-a936a5129513" corresp="#f726e635-bd5c-4d23-a6e6-35bd5c4d239a" type="editorial">Auf einer <ref target="https://edition-humboldt.de/H9679981/6r">aufgeklebten Notiz</ref> am Ende des Briefes diskutiert
                                    Humboldt die Höhe von <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0009370 https://www.geonames.org/1279685">Tibet</placeName>.</note></foreign></note><note place="mTop" hand="https://edition-humboldt.de/#addressee"><foreign xml:lang="deu">Hooker nach der Rück<supplied cert="high">k</supplied>unft</foreign></note><list>
                        <item>1. The Plains of <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0006686 https://www.geonames.org/1269750">India</placeName><choice>
                                <orig>.</orig>
                                <reg/>
                            </choice> &amp; <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0010808 https://www.geonames.org/1202950">Gange</placeName>tic
                            <lb/>valley from <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0016218 https://www.geonames.org/1275004">Calcutta</placeName> to the
                                <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0018784 https://www.geonames.org/1255729">Soane</placeName><pb n="2v"/>with its
                            mountains &amp;c &amp;c.</item>
                        <item>2. The <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0006863 https://www.geonames.org/1252558">Himalayah</placeName> &amp;
                                <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H1460789">U’Tsang</placeName>.</item>
                        <item>3. Eastern <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0005199 https://www.geonames.org/1252881">Bengal</placeName>, including
                            <lb/>the <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H2759692 https://www.geonames.org/1266856">Cossyah</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H4389850 https://www.geonames.org/1268810">Jyntea</placeName>, <del rendition="#erased">&amp;
                                </del><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H5532789 https://www.geonames.org/1275009">Cachar</persName> &amp;
                                <lb/><placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0010417 https://www.geonames.org/1477362">Sylhet</placeName> – the <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H1677321">Megna</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H4324469 https://www.geonames.org/1186937">Soonderbund</placeName>, <lb/>&amp; <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H5534643 https://www.geonames.org/1205733">Chittagong</placeName> districts. –</item>
                    </list></p>
                <p><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003944 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117351946">D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi>. Thomson</persName>
                    proposes also <lb/>publishing<add place="intralinear">,</add> at once<add place="intralinear">,</add> his travels <lb/>in <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0005093 https://www.geonames.org/1183616">Bultistan</placeName>, the <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0017455 https://www.geonames.org/7449791">Karakorum</placeName>
                    <lb/>&amp; <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000378 https://www.geonames.org/1440268">Kashmir</placeName>. Countries which
                        <lb/><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0002841 http://d-nb.info/gnd/12399523X">Vigne</persName> &amp; <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0012041 http://d-nb.info/gnd/11894343X">Hugel</persName> partially visited <lb/>&amp; have very
                    imperfectly described, <lb/>&amp; from which <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003944 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117351946">Thomson</persName>, after <lb/>a 2 years residence, has brought <lb/>great
                    stores of Collections &amp; <lb/>information. – Observations &amp;c.</p>
                <p>The <orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0016794 https://d-nb.info/gnd/2052078-5"><choice>
                            <abbr>E. Ind. Coy.</abbr>
                            <expan>East India Company</expan>
                        </choice></orgName> are about to <lb/>give <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003944 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117351946">D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi> Thomson</persName> the means of<pb n="3r"/>publishing &amp; distributing his <lb/>collections – after which perhaps
                    <lb/>my <choice>
                        <sic>Goverment</sic>
                        <corr>Government</corr>
                    </choice> may look more <lb/>liberally upon me.</p>
                <p>I have had more information <lb/><hi rendition="#mMM">about <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H1460789">U’Tsang</placeName> from <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0012858 http://viaf.org/viaf/68144648417618811837">D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi> Campbell</persName>: <lb/>There are <hi rendition="#u">no plains at all</hi>
                        <lb/>properly speaking – only <hi rendition="#u">flat</hi>
                        <lb/>bottomed valleys of <measure quantity="10000" unit="foot">10</measure>–<measure quantity="15000" unit="foot">1<subst>
                                <del rendition="#ow">4</del>
                                <add place="across">5</add>
                            </subst>000 <choice>
                                <abbr>ft</abbr>
                                <expan>feet</expan>
                            </choice></measure></hi>
                    <lb/>elevation, bounded by lofty &amp; <lb/>rugged mountains. Cultivation
                    <lb/>is confined to these narrow <lb/>valleys – There is no such thing <lb/>as a
                    level road<add place="intralinear">,</add> except along the <lb/>bottom of a
                    deep valley. <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003944 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117351946">Thomson</persName>
                    <lb/>says it is the same thing in <lb/><placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0005093 https://www.geonames.org/1183616">Bultistan</placeName> – Undulating noeuds<choice>
                        <orig>’</orig>
                        <reg/>
                    </choice>
                    <lb/>like <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0034174">Deotsu</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0018705 https://www.geonames.org/1280615"><subst>
                            <del rendition="#ow">I</del>
                            <add place="across">M</add>
                        </subst>ansarovar</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H5217773">Cholamoo</placeName>
                    <lb/>&amp;c are <hi rendition="#u">very rare</hi> – I have been <lb/>repeatedly
                    assured that Lake <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H3575191">Yarbro <lb/>Y<unclear cert="medium" reason="illegible">umtse</unclear></placeName><choice>
                        <orig>.</orig>
                        <reg/>
                    </choice>
                    <pb n="3v"/>is surrounded with <choice>
                        <abbr>Mts.</abbr>
                        <expan>Mountains</expan>
                    </choice><add place="intralinear">,</add> which <lb/>run in<add place="intralinear">,</add> as promontories<add place="intralinear">,</add>
                    all round<supplied cert="high">.</supplied>
                    <lb/>The I<unclear reason="covered" cert="medium"><subst>
                            <del rendition="#ow">n</del>
                            <add place="across">s</add>
                        </subst></unclear>land is very small indeed <lb/>at the <choice>
                        <abbr>S.W.</abbr>
                        <expan>Southwest</expan>
                    </choice>
                    <subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">m</del>
                        <add place="across">M</add>
                    </subst>argin. I have a <lb/>curious native map of <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0009370 https://www.geonames.org/1279685">Thibet</placeName><add place="intralinear">,</add>
                    <lb/>made by Lamas.<space dim="horizontal"/>
                    <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0004092 http://d-nb.info/gnd/129956252">Turner</persName>
                    <lb/>gives the <subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">m</del>
                        <add place="across">O</add>
                    </subst>ctober temperature <lb/>of <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H3683728 https://www.geonames.org/1279715">Digarchi</placeName> (alias <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H3683728 https://www.geonames.org/1279715">Shigatzi</placeName>
                    or <lb/><placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H7121702">Teshoo Loombo</placeName>) 5°–7<choice>
                        <orig>.</orig>
                        <reg/>
                    </choice>° &amp; not <lb/><hi rendition="#uu"><placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011427 http://www.geonames.org/1280737">Lhassa</placeName></hi><note place="left" hand="#author">There are many
                        (&amp; snowy) <choice>
                            <abbr>Mts</abbr>
                            <expan>Mountains</expan>
                        </choice> crossed between <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H3683728 https://www.geonames.org/1279715">Shigatzi</placeName>
                        &amp; <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011427 http://www.geonames.org/1280737">Lhassa</placeName><supplied cert="high">,</supplied> deep <lb/>valleys, no plains &amp; little
                        cultivation.</note> – which is always said <lb/>to be lower &amp; warmer,
                    but all <lb/>deny <name type="plant" subtype="vernacular" key="Vitis">vines</name> growing there (at <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011427 http://www.geonames.org/1280737">Lhassa</placeName>)<supplied cert="high">.</supplied>
                    <lb/>I have ripe <name type="plant" key="Prunus armeniaca">Apricot</name> stones
                    brought <lb/>by those who assure me that no <lb/><name type="plant" subtype="vernacular" key="Vitis">grapes</name> are grown.<space dim="horizontal"/> The <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0010714 https://www.geonames.org/1208092">Dzambo
                        <lb/>tcheu</placeName> takes a great Northerly <lb/>bend from East of
                        <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H3683728 https://www.geonames.org/1279715">Shigatzi</placeName>
                    <lb/>&amp; turns South again.</p>
                <p>I have been travelling in <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0010167 https://www.geonames.org/2638360">Scotland</placeName>
                    <pb n="5r"/>with my newly married <lb/><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H9236694 https://viaf.org/viaf/198146998388318941056">wife</persName>!
                    – an event upon which <lb/>I am sure you congratulate <lb/>me. My <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H9236694 https://viaf.org/viaf/198146998388318941056">wife</persName> is the daughter <lb/>of <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H1045743 https://d-nb.info/gnd/117517496">Professor Henslow</persName> of <orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000595 http://d-nb.info/gnd/7877-3">Cambridge</orgName><supplied cert="high">,</supplied>
                    <lb/>a Lady of accomplishments &amp; <lb/>great attachment to Physical
